{"schemaVersion":1,"bookId":"situational-15000","unitId":"scene-446","title":"庭外纠纷调解","sectionId":"chapter-20","sectionTitle":"依法办事不出错","pageStart":2196,"pageEnd":2200,"extractionMethod":"text-layer","wordEntryCount":10,"duplicateEntryCount":21,"pages":[{"number":2196,"blocks":[{"type":"title","text":"446 庭外纠纷调解"},{"type":"section","text":"Step1 场景词"},{"type":"entry","text":"conflict resolution解决冲突","headword":"conflict resolution"}]},{"number":2197,"blocks":[{"type":"entry","text":"mediator [ˈmiːdieɪtə(r)]","headword":"mediator"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.调停者；斡旋者，解决纠争的人（或机构）"},{"type":"entry","text":"arbitral tribunal 仲裁法庭","headword":"arbitral tribunal"},{"type":"entry","text":"neutral third party 中立第三方","headword":"neutral third party"},{"type":"entry","text":"binding [ˈbaɪndɪŋ]","headword":"binding"},{"type":"definition","text":"a.有法律约束力的"}]},{"number":2198,"blocks":[{"type":"entry","text":"waiver [ˈweɪvə(r)]","headword":"waiver"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.（对合法权利或要求的）弃权；弃权声明"},{"type":"entry","text":"contradictory [ˌkɒntrəˈdɪktəri]","headword":"contradictory"},{"type":"definition","text":"a.互相矛盾的，互相对立的"},{"type":"note","text":"◎contradictory relationship矛盾关系"},{"type":"entry","text":"contradictory statement互相矛盾的说法","headword":"contradictory statement"}]},{"number":2199,"blocks":[{"type":"entry","text":"indemnity insurance赔偿保险","headword":"indemnity insurance"},{"type":"entry","text":"quittance [ˈkwɪtns]","headword":"quittance"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.（债务等的）免除"},{"type":"section","text":"Step2 学以致用"},{"type":"section","text":"Conversation 1"},{"type":"example","text":"A：Didn't Bruce owe you some money? What happened?（布鲁斯不"},{"type":"text","text":"是欠你钱吗？发生什么事情了？）"},{"type":"example","text":"B：He skipped out on his debt. （他因还不了债而躲起来了。）"},{"type":"section","text":"Conversation 2"},{"type":"example","text":"A：What's the work of a mediator? （调停者的工作是什么？）"}]},{"number":2200,"blocks":[{"type":"example","text":"B：He talks to the two who are quarrelling and makes them reach an"},{"type":"text","text":"agreement.（他与争吵的双方交流，并使他们达成一致。）"}]}]}